efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: AMORTIZED O(1)
space complexity: O(N)
explanation: Utilizes two stacks to simulate a queue. Push operations are O(1) as they directly append to the input stack. Pop, peek, and empty operations are O(N) in the worst case when transferring elements from the input stack to the output stack. However, these transfers occur infrequently, leading to an amortized time complexity of O(1) over a sequence of operations. Space complexity is O(N) due to the potential storage of all elements in the stacks.

